field.name: SeqNum
field.description: Sequence number as assigned to message

field.name: UUID
field.description: Matches Establish.UUID used to establish the connection

field.name: SenderID
field.description: Operator ID. Should be unique per Firm ID. Assigned value used to identify specific message originator. Represents last individual or team in charge of the system which modifies the order before submission to the Globex platform, or if not modified from initiator (party role=118), last individual or team in charge of the system, which submit the order to the Globex platform

field.name: PartyDetailsListReqID
field.description: The unique identifier of the PartyDetailsDefinitionRequestAck attached to this message; pancake flip of what was submitted on inbound message

field.name: TransactTime
field.description: Time of execution/order creation; expressed in UTC.

field.name: SendingTimeEpoch
field.description: Time when the message is sent. 64-bit integer expressing the number of nano seconds since midnight January 1, 1970.

field.name: OrderRequestID
field.description: OrderRequestID used to identify an OrderMassActionRequest and echo the value on the corresponding OrderMassActionReport

field.name: MassActionReportID
field.description: Unique ID of Order Mass Action Report as assigned by CME. If fragmented then all messages must have the same value.

field.name: MassActionType
field.description: Specifies the type of action requested. Constant value

field.name: SecurityGroup
field.description: Specifies the Product Group for which working orders should be cancelled. Conditionally present if MassActionScope=Product Group (Tag1374=10).

field.name: Location
field.description: Text describing sender's location (i.e. geopraphic location and/or desk)

field.name: SecurityID
field.description: Conditionally present if MassActionScope=Instrument (Tag 1374=1)

field.name: DelayDuration
field.description: Not being used currently

field.name: MassActionResponse
field.description: Specifies the action taken by CME when it received the Order Mass Action Request.

field.name: ManualOrderIndicator
field.description: Indicates if the order was initially received manually (as opposed to electronically)

field.name: MassActionScope
field.description: Specifies the scope of the action

field.name: TotalAffectedOrders
field.description: Total number of orders affected by the Order Mass Action Request. Will be returned as zero for rejects or if request is accepted but no orders could be cancelled. If fragmented then this is the sum of NoAffectedOrders across all messages with the same MassActionReportID. Otherwise will have same value as NoAffectedOrders when one or more orders is cancelled.

field.name: LastFragment
field.description: Indicates whether the message is the last message in a sequence of messages to support fragmentation

field.name: MassActionRejectReason
field.description: Reason Order Mass Action Request was rejected. Required if Mass Action Response=0.

field.name: MarketSegmentID
field.description: Specifies the market segment (physical match engine partition) for which working orders should be cancelled. Conditionally present if MassActionScope=Market Segment (Tag 1374=9)

field.name: MassCancelRequestType
field.description: If present specifies the scope of the OrderMassActionRequest within the context of Session and Firm. If absent then all orders belonging to Session and Firm combination will be cancelled for specified MassActionScope

field.name: Side
field.description: f provided then only orders belonging to one side will be cancelled. If absent then orders belonging to both sides will be cancelled

field.name: OrdType
field.description: If provided then only orders of this type will be cancelled. If absent then all order types will be cancelled

field.name: TimeInForce
field.description: If provided then only orders with this qualifier will be cancelled. If absent then all Day & GT orders will be cancelled

field.name: SplitMsg
field.description: Indicates whether a message was delayed as a result of being split among multiple packets (0) or if a message was delayed as a result of TCP re-transmission (1) or if a complete message was delayed due to a previously submitted split or out of order message (2). If absent then the message was not delayed and was neither split nor received out of order

field.name: LiquidityFlag
field.description: Represents the market making MiFID obligation reporting

field.name: PossRetransFlag
field.description: Flags message as possible retransmission. This will convey whether a message is an original transmission or duplicate in response to RetransmissionRequest. This will become pertinent when original messages get interleaved with Retransmission responses

field.name: DelayToTime
field.description: Indicates the amount of time that a message was delayed as a result of being split (9553=0) or as a result of being out of order due to TCP retransmission (9553=1) or as a result of being queued behind a split message (9553=2). Represented as number of nanoseconds in unix epoch format (since Jan 1, 1970). Subtracting this number from FIFO time will represent original received time of delayed message

group.name: NoAffectedOrders
group.description: Total number of order identifiers affected by the OrderMass Action Request. Only used if orders could actually be cancelled otherwise will be set to zero. Must be followed by OrigCIOrdID

field.name: OrigCIOrdID
field.description: Contains the ClOrd of the cancelled order

field.name: AffectedOrderID
field.description: Order ID of an order cancelled by a mass action request.

field.name: CxlQuantity
field.description: Total quantity cancelled for this order.

field.name: SendingTimeEpoch

field.name: CancelledSymbol

field.name: Location
field.description: Text describing sender's location (i.e. geopraphic location and/or desk)
